<p>Thymosin Beta-4 is one of the most abundant intracellular peptides in the human body. It's present in nearly every tissue, with concentrations spiking dramatically at injury sites. When you cut your skin, strain a tendon, or damage heart muscle, TB-4 is one of the first molecular responders.</p>

<p>Unlike many synthetic peptides, TB-4 is a natural compound your body already produces. White blood cells and platelets release it locally during healing. It doesn't circulate like a hormone; it acts right where it's needed.</p>

<div class="d">
